  "text": "In this section, we describe and analyse the sink-popping algorithm by Cohn, Pemantle, and Propp [CITATION_1] . The goal is to sample a sink-free orientation in an undirected graph. This problem was introduced by Bubley and Dyer [CITATION_2] as an early showcase of the power of path coupling for Markov chains [CITATION_3] . This problem was also reintroduced more recently to show lower bounds for distributed Lovász local lemma algorithms [BFH + 16], where the goal is to find, instead of to sample, a sink-free orientation.",
